`Comparable<T>` is a built-in interface for natural ordering. Implement `compareTo()` and `Arrays.sort()` / `Collections.sort()` work automatically:

```java
@Override
public int compareTo(Student other) {
    return this.grade - other.grade;  // ascending order
}
```

Return negative: this comes first. Return positive: other comes first. Return 0: equal.

